# Format: You will use the following starter code to write the solution to the problem and enclose your code within delimiters.\n```python\nclass Solution:\n    def findDifference(self, nums1: List[int], nums2: List[int]) -> List[List[int]]:\n        \n```\n\n### Answer: (use the provided format with backticks)\n", "response": "```python\nfrom typing import List\n\nclass Solution:\n    def findDifference(self, nums1: List[int], nums2: List[int]) -> List[List[int]]:\n        # Convert lists to sets to find distinct elements and perform set operations\n        set1 = set(nums1)\n        set2 = set(nums2)\n        \n        # Find elements in nums1 that are not in nums2\n        diff1 = list(set1 - set2)\n        \n        # Find elements in nums2 that are not in nums1\n        diff2 = list(set2 - set1)\n        \n        return [diff1, diff2]\n```\n\nThis solution uses set operations to efficiently find the distinct elements in each list that are not present in the other list. The time complexity is O(n + m), where n and m are the lengths of `nums1` and `nums2`, respectively. The space complexity is also O(n + m) due to the storage of the sets and the result lists.", "estimated_date": 1648339200000}